  "title": "3D Designer (Spatial and Exhibition design) #79386",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Design and Build Service Provider</li><li>Position Title: <strong>3D Designer (Commercial / Event)</strong></li><li>Working Location: North - Admiralty</li><li>Working Hours: 5.5 days / Mon-Fri: 9am-6pm, Sat: 9am-1pm</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Up to SGD 4000 + AWS + Performance Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Work closely with the creative team, sales personnel, and project owners/managers to conceptualize and design engaging and impactful experiences</li><li>Oversee the entire design process from initial concept to final execution, transforming ideas into visually compelling and functional 3D designs</li><li>Produce high-quality 3D renderings that clearly convey design intent and storytelling</li><li>Apply strong knowledge of design principles, spatial planning, and user experience to develop immersive environments tailored to target audiences</li><li>Stay updated on industry trends, emerging technologies, and best practices to deliver innovative and forward-thinking design solutions</li><li>Participate in client presentations, effectively communicating design ideas and incorporating feedback to refine and enhance outcomes</li><li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams including graphic designers, technical consultants, and draftsmen to ensure cohesive integration of all design elements</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Min. Diploma in 3D design, industrial design, architecture, or a related field</li><li>Min. 2 years of experience in 3D design with a strong portfolio highlighting outstanding spatial and exhibition design work</li><li>Proficiency in industry-standard design software, including but not limited to, AutoCAD, SketchUp, Adobe Creative Suite, Rhino, V-Ray, and other relevant tools</li><li>Training is provided to inexperienced candidate</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#79386 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Rachael Lee | EA Reg No.: R2093131</p>",
